                          "value": {
                            "type": "constant", 
                            "value": "<b>Texture</b>: If you were standing on a beach covered with rocks, the rocks close to you would be well defined, the cracks and patterns easy to see, but the rocks far away would appear less defined. We use information about texture to tell us about distance as well. Objects close up should have a lot of texture, whereas identical objects farther away should have less."
