                        }, 
                        {
                          "name": "caption", 
                          "value": {
                            "type": "constant", 
                            "value": "<b>Linear Perspective</b>: Whenever you have parallel lines, such as the rails on a railroad track, they will appear to get closer in the distance. Even though the lines never actually touch, the appearance of converging lines tells the brain that the lines are getting farther away."
