                        {
                          "name": "caption", 
                          "value": {
                            "type": "constant", 
                            "value": "<b>Aerial Perspective</b>: Have you ever looked far off into the distance and noticed that objects seem a little hazy or washed out? That\u2019s because between you and that far-away mountain range is a lot of air filled with dirt, smog, fog, and dust. The brain assumes that objects that appear hazy must be farther away and clearer objects must be closer."
